to back up your story.
- You could.

686
01:03:14,130 --> 01:03:16,690
I won't.

687
01:03:16,766 --> 01:03:20,634
They'll make you because
your lies won't stand up to the truth.

688
01:03:25,908 --> 01:03:29,366
- I wouldn't do this if I were you.
-[ Door Closes ]

689
01:03:34,050 --> 01:03:36,075
That's it.

690
01:03:36,152 --> 01:03:40,452
I mean, if you got
any, uh, questions, then--

691
01:03:40,523 --> 01:03:42,957
One or two.

692
01:03:43,025 --> 01:03:47,985
You see, we don't actually
have any unsolved murders
of old ladies at the present.

693
01:03:48,064 --> 01:03:53,297
- You must have.
- There's no such ongoing investigation.

694
01:03:53,369 --> 01:03:56,497
And we don't know
this Mr. Cobb of yours.

695
01:03:57,940 --> 01:04:00,101
I warned you
he'd look in the envelope.

696
01:04:00,176 --> 01:04:03,304
He gave me his word.
I believed him.

697
01:04:03,379 --> 01:04:05,677
It's nothing personal.
He couldn't help it.

698
01:04:05,748 --> 01:04:08,239
I mean, he's a born peeper.

699
01:04:11,521 --> 01:04:14,649
Anyway, down to business.

700
01:04:14,724 --> 01:04:16,988
[ Scoffs ]
Business?

701
01:04:18,861 --> 01:04:20,988
[ Policeman ]
Perhaps there's...

702
01:04:21,063 --> 01:04:24,157
something else
you'd like to tell me, hmm?

703
01:04:24,233 --> 01:04:26,497
Anything?

704
01:04:29,672 --> 01:04:32,163
- Where's the hammer?
- It's in that bag.

705
01:04:34,644 --> 01:04:38,341
What are you gonna
do with it?

706
01:04:38,414 --> 01:04:41,474
The old man was very specific
about how I should do things.

707
01:04:43,085 --> 01:04:45,610
Wh-- What's the old man
got to say about it?

708
01:04:45,688 --> 01:04:48,885
Oh, well, he is letting me
keep all the money from his safe.

709
01:04:50,293 --> 01:04:52,454
Anything at all?

710
01:04:52,528 --> 01:04:55,656
Your side of things?

711
01:04:55,731 --> 01:04:59,633
He says your demands
have become too unreasonable.

712
01:04:59,702 --> 01:05:01,897
You've become too greedy
in your blackmail.

713
01:05:01,971 --> 01:05:04,633
He said something about
you being a witness...

714
01:05:04,707 --> 01:05:07,175
to an incident that happened
in this very room.

715
01:05:07,243 --> 01:05:11,202
He was very precise about exactly how
and where I should take care of things.

716
01:05:11,280 --> 01:05:16,479
Something about a bloodstained
carpet that you've got stashed
away to back up your story,

717
01:05:16,552 --> 01:05:19,612
should it ever be told.

718
01:05:19,689 --> 01:05:24,319
- Did you talk to her?
- We found her this morning.

719
01:05:24,393 --> 01:05:27,055
[ Screaming ]

720
01:05:27,129 --> 01:05:31,327
- What do you mean, "found her?"
- Her body.

721
01:05:31,400 --> 01:05:35,029
We also found a hammer
with two types of blood on it.

722
01:05:35,104 --> 01:05:40,007
One type, I assume, will match
the bloke you put in hospital.

723
01:05:40,076 --> 01:05:44,570
All her fingers were smashed.
You must have tortured her
to get the combination.

724
01:05:44,647 --> 01:05:47,810
I didn't touch her!

725
01:05:47,883 --> 01:05:53,412
We also found some
interesting items in your flat
in this shoe box under your bed.

726
01:05:53,489 --> 01:05:57,755
Among various items reported missing
by the deceased last week, we found...

727
01:05:57,827 --> 01:06:01,923
these pairs
of ladies' underwear.

728
01:06:01,998 --> 01:06:06,094
Were they hers? I assume
so since we found them stashed...

729
01:06:06,168 --> 01:06:09,035
with these passport-style
photographs of the deceased.

730
01:06:11,040 --> 01:06:14,373
We also found
this pearl earring...

731
01:06:14,443 --> 01:06:19,779
which exactly matched the one worn by
the deceased at the time of her death.

732
01:06:19,849 --> 01:06:22,340
- A little trophy?
- No!

733
01:06:22,418 --> 01:06:26,047
It was Cobb who planted it
when we turned over her place.

734
01:06:26,122 --> 01:06:28,852
Go and collar him.
I gave you his address.

735
01:06:30,493 --> 01:06:33,894
We checked the address you gave us.
There's no Cobb there.

736
01:06:33,963 --> 01:06:38,059
The flat belongs to
a Mister...

737
01:06:38,134 --> 01:06:40,068
D. Lloyd.

738
01:06:41,470 --> 01:06:43,597
He's just returned
from holiday.

739
01:06:43,673 --> 01:06:47,439
And he told us that while
he was away, his flat had been burgled.

740
01:06:47,510 --> 01:06:50,638
Not much was missing.

741
01:06:50,713 --> 01:06:53,273
But his new credit card
hasn't yet arrived.

742
01:06:53,349 --> 01:06:58,377
Well, that was Cobb! We used it
to pay for a meal in a restaurant.

743
01:06:58,454 --> 01:07:00,718
We found this
at your flat.

744
01:07:00,790 --> 01:07:03,315
It was Cobb...

745
01:07:05,361 --> 01:07:07,386
who stole it.

746
01:07:07,463 --> 01:07:09,829
Is that your handwriting?

747
01:07:12,301 --> 01:07:14,235
Yes.

